text.section:
An order for guardianship of an individual:
except as otherwise provided in this subtitle, § 4-414 of the Estates and Trusts Article, and § 2-123 of the Real Property Article, terminates a parent's duties, obligations, and rights toward the individual;
eliminates the need for a further consent by a parent to adoption of the individual;
grants a local department guardianship with the right to consent to the individual's adoption or other planned permanent living arrangement; and
terminates the individual's CINA case.

section.section:
Unless a juvenile court orders otherwise and subject to review by the juvenile court, a child's guardian may make all decisions affecting the child's education, health, and welfare, including consenting:
to adoption of the child;
to application by the child for a driver's license;
to enlistment by the child in the armed forces;
to marriage of the child; and
subject to subparagraphs (ii) and (iii) of this paragraph, to medical, psychiatric, or surgical treatment.

A child's guardian:
may have the child admitted to an inpatient psychiatric facility in accordance with the standards for emergency commitment in § 10-617 of the Health - General Article for not more than 20 days;
except as provided in item 1 of this subparagraph, may not place the child in an inpatient psychiatric facility without express authorization of the juvenile court.
